# Payments Module Implementation Plan

This plan details the development of the Payments module for Club 33.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Database Schema Changes**: I will be using a single `payments` table with a `category` field to distinguish between Club Fees (Cuota), Gear (Indumentaria), and other types. This avoids table fragmentation.

## Proposed Changes

### [Database & Types]

#### [MODIFY] [types/index.ts](file:///g:/gestion33/src/types/index.ts)
- Add `fee_status` and `gear_status` to [Player](file:///g:/gestion33/src/types/index.ts#1-55).
- Expand [Payment](file:///g:/gestion33/src/types/index.ts#56-69) type with `period_month` and `period_year`.
- Add fee configuration fields to [ClubSettings](file:///g:/gestion33/src/types/index.ts#101-117).

### [Configuration]

#### [MODIFY] [settings/page.tsx](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/settings/page.tsx)
- Add "Configuración de Pagos" section.
- Inputs for: Cuota Mensual ($), Cuota Anual ($), Descuento Anual (%), Precio Indumentaria ($).
- Implement automatic `annual_fee` calculation when `monthly_fee` or `annual_discount_percent` changes.
- Add a helper function to perform the calculation: `monthly_fee * 12 * (1 - discount/100)`.

### [Payments Dashboard]

#### [NEW] [payments/page.tsx](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/payments/page.tsx)
- Summary cards: Total recaudado este mes, Pendientes, Al día vs Atrasados.
- Table listing all payments with filters by category and player.
- Modal to "Registrar Pago".
- [FIX] Update [loadData](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/payments/page.tsx#51-66) to fetch players from the `players` table instead of `profiles`.
- [FIX] Ensure the `X` close button in the modal correctly triggers `setShowAddModal(false)`.
- [ENHANCE] Update the dashboard table to list players and their current payment status (monthly/annual) using notification icons similar to the documentation module.
- [ENHANCE] Add "Pago Anual" as an option in the category selection.

### [Player Detail Integration]

#### [MODIFY] [players/detail/[id]/page.tsx](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/players/detail/[id]/page.tsx)
- Add "Pagos" tab.
- History table for the specific player.
- Status badges: "Al día" / "Atrasado" for fees, "Pagado" / "Entregado" for gear.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` to ensure type safety.

### Manual Verification
1.  Set fees in Settings and verify they are saved.
2.  Register a monthly fee for a player and check if their status updates to "Al día".
3.  Register a gear payment and verify the delivery status can be toggled.
- Manual verification of player list in dropdown.
- Check annual fee update in UI when parameters change.
- Verify status icons in the payments table.

### [Manual User Creation]

#### [MODIFY] [users/page.tsx](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/users/page.tsx)
- Add a toggle or tabs in the "Nuevo Personal" modal to switch between "Enviar Invitación" (Email) and "Creación Manual" (Name/Password).
- For Manual Creation, add fields for `full_name` and `password`.
- Update [handleAddSubmit](file:///g:/gestion33/src/app/dashboard/payments/page.tsx#82-121) to handle both methods.
- Implement `handleManualCreate` using Supabase Auth (Sign Up) and then creating the profile.

#### [NEW] [adminService.ts](file:///g:/gestion33/src/services/adminService.ts)
- Create a service to handle administrative actions like manual user creation.
- Note: Manual creation via `admin.auth.createUser` requires a Service Role Key, which shouldn't be on the client. Alternatively, use a standard `signUp` with a placeholder email (like `username@gestion33.com`) if the user only wants "Name and Password".
- *Correction*: The user said "only name and password". In Supabase, Auth requires an email or phone for standard signup. I will propose using a formatted email based on the name (e.g., `name@club33.com`) or asking the user if they want to use a "Username" field that maps to email internally.
